FBIS4-43455 "drweu117_p_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 GREECE Papandreou Comments on Territorial Waters Issue Papandreou Comments on Territorial Waters Issue NC1606164494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1500 GMT 16 Jun 94 NC1606164494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] President Konstandinos Karamanlis today received Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou, who briefed him on questions of domestic and foreign policy, economic developments, the Balkan situation, domestic developments, and on the topics to be discussed at the European Union [EU] summit to be held in Corfu on 24 June. Yeoryios Koyiannis has the following report. [Begin recording] Domestic political and economic developments as well as the whole spectrum of international issues were the subject of the meeting between Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou and President Konstandinos Karamanlis at noon today in the Presidential Palace. As the prime minister said, the meeting lasted for one hour and, as always, it was held in a friendly atmosphere. Mr. Papandreou briefed the president on the EU summit to be held in Corfu and the topics to be discussed. He also briefed Mr. Karamanlis on his intention to proceed with a government reshuffle which he scheduled for after the Corfu summit. The prime minister also spoke to correspondents about the U.S. State Department's statement, according to which Greece is not entitled to a 10-mile national airspace but only six miles, the limit of its territorial waters. Responding to a question from a correspondent, the prime minister said that this has always been the U.S. position. Mr. Papandreou added: However, it has been historically established that we have a 10-mile airspace and not six miles, the limit of our territorial waters. This is something that is not going to change. [end recording]
